        <div1 type="summary">
            <p><add hand="#barker">Land. Trade.</add></p>
        </div1>
        <div1 type="body">
            

<p>for the <placeName>League on the Sn Byrnard</placeName> which you wrote me that I
Could have I have sent out <persName>whiteside</persName>s obligation for two hundred
Dollars payable in good american horses or mules, if that will answer
your perpose in payment of my Land, my <persName>son </persName>will let you have it&#8212;</p>

<p>Sir you will please write to me <persName>Mr Allcorn</persName> arived in <placeName>Nachitoches</placeName>
on this <date n="05-1-1824">5th of this instant</date>, your <persName>brother </persName>and <persName>sister </persName>has not yet
arived, my anxiety is extreamly great to git on to that Country, I
have several <persName>Brothers </persName>that writes me they will be on from <placeName>Kentuckey</placeName>
one of them will leave this <date n="Winter-1824">winter</date>,&#8212;</p>

<p>we have nothing new in this Country times is hard and money
scarce</p>

<p>no more but remains your most obedient</p>

<p>Friend and well wisher   </p>

<p><persName>Martin All[en]</persName></p>

        </div1>
